      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName)
        Reads the provided Design Checkpoint file and load the the logical netlist (EDIF) and placement and routing information (XDEF) stored inside the ZIP archive (DCP=ZIP). If the .EDF file inside the .DCP file is binary (encrypted) or not present, it will search for an .EDF file of the same base name as the .DCP file name in the same directory where the .DCP file resides. If no EDIF file is found, a RuntimeException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the Design Checkpoint file to read into RapidWright.
        Returns:
        The populated design read from the checkpoint file.

      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName,
                                    java.lang.String edfFileName,
                                    boolean skipXdef,
                                    CodePerfTracker t)
        Reads the provided Design Checkpoint file and load the the logical netlist (EDIF) and placement and routing information (XDEF) stored inside the ZIP archive (DCP=ZIP). If edfFileName is null, it will load the .EDF file inside the .DCP file. If the .EDF file is binary (encrypted) or not present, it will search for an .EDF file of the same base name as the .DCP file name in the same directory where the .DCP file resides. If no EDIF file is found, a RuntimeException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the dcp file to load.
        edfFileName - Name of an explicit EDIF file to load (overrides internal DCP)
        skipXdef - If true, will not load an XDEF file, if available or external EDIF of the same basename.
        Returns:
        The populated design read from the checkpoint file.

      • extractFileFromDCP

        public static boolean extractFileFromDCP(java.lang.String dcpFileName,
                                         java.lang.String outputFileName,
                                         java.lang.String suffix)
        Extracts the first file matching the pattern from the DCP provided.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the DCP file to extract from.
        outputFileName - The name of the newly extracted file from the DCP.
        suffix - A file extension to match against. If the file extension matches more than one entry in the DCP file, it will only extract the first.
        Returns:
        True if a file was successfully extracted, false otherwise.
